# Node / Bun runtime — production build hygiene

This project uses **Bun** with an exact version pin (`package.json` `packageManager`). Older Node.js defaults (e.g. 16.x) cause Next.js and CI images to fail with discontinued-runtime errors.

## The rule

1. **package.json**: keep `engines.node` on a supported LTS (e.g. `20.x`) and align `packageManager` / `.bun-version` with the Bun version used in CI.
2. **CI / Azure / Cloudflare pipelines**: use Node 20+ images where `node` runs (App Service, GitHub Actions `setup-node`, etc.).
3. **Local**: optional `.nvmrc` with `20` for consistency.

## Supported Node (typical)

| Version | Status |
|---------|--------|
| 16.x | Discontinued for many hosts — avoid |
| 20.x | LTS — preferred floor |
| 22.x | Supported |

## Detection

Run `bun run build` locally before pushing; fix `engines` mismatches before they reach CI.
